5 minutes Keto meal!!! Pizza, Pastrami and Cheese shell Egg

You can make tacos, tostadas, chips and a few other things with cheese shells!⁣
.
😕 Don't know how to start keto diet properly? or want to lose 5-10 lbs in the first week alone with keto lifestyle ?
You can click link in our bio to get Everything You Need for keto Success. Imagine… armed with 4-week meal plan, 7 Keto guide books, and the 3 bonus guides… you’ll be able to start strong and finish strong. 💪 @keto.recipes_
⏩ Don't forget to share and follow @keto.recipes_ for more 😃
.

Which have you tried making? Did you love?😃⁣
⁣
Would you add meat or just the egg?⁣
⁣
BTW you don’t need a griddle, it can be made in a pan too.⁣
⁣
What about my one handed egg cracker skills #imissedmycalling 😂⁣
⁣
Don’t forget to share this easy meal idea with friends starting keto 👏⁣

To make:⁣
-add about 1/2 cup shredded cheese to a hot skillet⁣
-add your toppings of choice and let the cheese brown a bit. You can flip it over so you get it crispy on both sides or put a lid on it and it will steam the toppings and crisp the bottom👌⁣

KETO CHICKEN NUGGETS 😋🙌 by @ketosnackz  

Ingredients:
1 can of chicken
1 large egg
1/2 cup shredded cheese
Seasonings of choice

Instructions:
1. Mash your chicken up in a bowl and mix with all ingredients.
2. Shape into nuggets and air fry on parchment paper at 400F for 8-10 minutes flipping halfway through.
3. Let cool & enjoy!

Notes: You can also bake at 400F for 20 mins on parchment paper flipping halfway.

What are your must have burger toppings??
.
This is one of my favorite ways to do lower carb & higher protein. These little mini baby lettuce icebergs are the perfect size to hold in your hand.
.
I went with some Gouda cheese and fresh jalapeño slices (with seeds of course) because I wanted an extra kick… all of of your toppings, cheese choices, and spice levels are at your discretion.
.
1. I used a baby iceberg lettuce from @josiesorganics as my base. I ordered it through @wholefoods on Amazon prime.
.
2.Topped with @kewpieusa mayo - my favorite.
.
3.Added fresh local heirloom tomatoes and red onion rings.
.
4.Added a well seasoned burger pattie. I add fresh finely ground onion to my meat blend for some added flavor
.
5.Topped with aged Gouda cheese
.
6.Added some jalapeño slices.
.
7.Add mustard, mayo, or any other condiment.
.
8.Slap on the top part of the lettuce.
.
Grab those napkins and devour. This was an “over the sink” lunch for me.
.
